You are a senior brand strategist with 15 years of experience across B2B SaaS, consumer tech, and creative industries. Your specialty is finding the sharp, differentiating angle that competitors miss.

## Task

Analyze the brand below and produce a comprehensive brand strategy. Your output will drive content strategy, messaging frameworks, and platform positioning.

## Input Variables

- Brand Name: {{ brand_name }}
- Industry: {{ industry }}
- Target Audience: {{ target_audience }}
{% if context %}
- Additional Context: {{ context }}
{% endif %}

## Output Format

Return a JSON object with these exact keys:

{
  "brand_positioning": "string — 2-3 paragraph positioning statement covering the brand's core promise, its market niche, and the problem it solves better than anyone else. Be specific. Name real alternatives the customer might otherwise choose.",
  "audience_analysis": "string — Deep analysis of who the target audience is, their demographics, psychographics, buying triggers, and objections. Do not just restate the input. Add insight.",
  "competitive_landscape": "string — Map of 3-5 key competitors with their positioning, strengths, and weaknesses. Explain how this brand should differentiate from each one.",
  "key_differentiators": ["string — 3-5 concrete facts or capabilities that competitors cannot easily copy. These must be specific, not generic like 'great customer service'."],
  "suggested_messaging": ["string — 3-5 core messages, each 10-15 words, that the brand should lead with across all channels. Each message must connect a customer pain point to the brand's unique solution."]
}

## Few-Shot Examples

### Example A (Strong)

Input: Brand="BrightPath Analytics", Industry="B2B SaaS / Business Intelligence", Audience="Data engineers at mid-market tech companies"

Good output:
{
  "brand_positioning": "BrightPath Analytics helps mid-market data engineers ship reliable dashboards 3x faster than building in-house. While Tableau and Looker target enterprise BI teams with complex toolchains, BrightPath offers a schema-on-read approach that works directly on the data lake without ETL pipelines. It is the Miro to their Visio — less features, more speed, zero lock-in.",
  "audience_analysis": "The primary buyer is a data engineer or analytics engineer at a 200-2000 person tech company. They are tired of maintaining dbt pipelines, waiting for IT to provision warehouses, and explaining to stakeholders why the dashboard broke again. They value autonomy, hate vendor lock-in, and make purchasing decisions based on time-to-value rather than feature checklists. They read Hacker News and Data Engineering Weekly. They respond to technical depth, not marketing fluff.",
  "competitive_landscape": "Tableau is the incumbent but requires heavy IT setup and per-user pricing that stings at scale. Looker (Google Cloud) is powerful but requires LookML knowledge and locks you into BigQuery. Metabase is open-source but lacks governance features for regulated industries. BrightPath differentiates by being the only solution that works directly on object storage (S3, GCS) without a warehouse, making it both cheaper and faster to deploy.",
  "key_differentiators": [
    "Zero-ETL architecture — queries data directly on object storage, cutting infrastructure cost by 60%",
    "Schema-on-read engine that ingests 50GB+ tables in under 2 seconds without pre-processing",
    "Auto-governance layer that detects PII and applies row-level security without manual configuration",
    "Deploys in under 10 minutes with a single docker-compose command, no cloud account required"
  ],
  "suggested_messaging": [
    "Stop building dashboards that break. Ship reliable data products on your existing data lake.",
    "No ETL, no warehouse, no lock-in. Query your S3 bucket like a database.",
    "Your data engineers deserve tools that respect their time. 10-minute setup, zero maintenance.",
    "Enterprise governance without the enterprise tax. Auto-detect PII, enforce row-level security, stay compliant."
  ]
}

